In this op-ed, President Obama and Prime Minister Cameron highlight the strong alliance between the United States and the United Kingdom. They emphasize the partnership of the heart that is bound by shared history, traditions, and values. The leaders discuss the joint efforts to address global challenges such as the economic recovery, the mission in Afghanistan, imposing sanctions on Iran, supporting democratic movements in the Middle East and North Africa, promoting development, and caring for veterans. They express confidence in the alliance's ability to achieve great things and emphasize their commitment to working together.